We only have one location for in-person absentee voting during the two weeks that in-person absentee voting is allowed. That location is Altoona City Hall, 1303 Lynn Avenue, Altoona, WI 54720. The dates are regulated per state statutes which starts the Monday, two weeks prior to an election and ends the Friday prior to the Tuesday election. For the November 8, 2016 election, in-person absentee voting will take place from Monday, October 24, 2016 and end on Friday, November 4, 2016. Since our regular office hours are Monday - Friday 7:30 - 4:00 p.m, absentee voting takes place from 8:00 a.m. - 4:00 p.m. during those two weeks. (5:00 p.m. on the last Friday which is November 4).
